Opal Labs, Inc.

Opal is the easiest way to share files with friends and colleagues securely. 






Stage

Prototype Ready



Industry

Internet / Web Services



Location

Los Angeles, CA, USA



Currency

USD



Founded

October 2013



Employees

2



Website

opal.io

















Company Summary





Opal is a private messaging and file sharing app secured with end-to-end encryption. It is an easy-to-use web app, so users don't need to download anything. Due to recent revelations about domestic spying, people are realizing that the tools they use are insecure, and are demanding secure, user-friendly alternatives. Specific target markets for Opal include healthcare professionals (who are bound by HIPAA), accountants, bankers, and lawyers.










Team













Nicolas Robert LaCasse

CEO




Nick has been a coding since he was a child.  He earned degrees from MIT and UCLA.  He's worked for two startups, and recently was senior engineer at OkCupid Labs.  He enjoys cooking and biking.












Jason Campbell

CTO/CFO




Jason is an expert in product design and development with almost 10 years of experience in the LA tech scene.  He founded JS.LA, LA's largest and most-loved javascript meetup.  He has a degree from UCSB, and enjoys biking and playing with his dog Frank.












